Peru Stocks: Alicorp, Cerro Verde, Ferreyros, Maple, Scotiabank

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-04T20:23:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/peru-stocks-alicorp-cerro-verde-ferreyros-maple-scotiabank.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. New York time.  The  Lima  General Index rose for a third session, adding 0.8
percent to 19,368.44. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 0.8
percent to 2,492.35.  Industrial and banking stocks gained as investors took
advantage of “cheaply-priced” shares, said Daniel Romero, an
analyst at Lima-based investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer,
jumped 5 percent to 14.60 soles after daily Gestion reported the
Gloria SA unit will produce ethanol at the end of the year.
 Alicorp SA (ALICORC1)  (ALICORC1 PE), Peru’s largest foodstuff maker, gained
2.8 percent to 5.60 soles.  Scotiabank Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1 PE), the
local unit of  Canada ’s third-largest bank, rose 2.7 percent to
46.50 soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based
distributor for Caterpillar Inc., climbed 2.3 percent to 2.70
soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, gained 2.3 percent to 91
cents.  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), Peru’s third-
largest copper producer, gained as the metal advanced in  London .
The Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc. unit rose 2 percent to
$36.20.  To contact the reporter on this story:
